newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: NWE products mixed, fuel oil clearly firmer.
newsitem.headline: NWE products mixed, fuel oil clearly firmer.

text.p: NWE oil products were mixed on Wednesday morning as futures losses reduced heating oil prices, but fuel oil clearly rose.

Early gasoline talk was slightly confused. Physical barge levels rose to $205/$207 fob ARA in thin trading. Dealers said the market had been sold very aggressively to suit a trading position and had simply edged back on Wednesday morning.
However, September Eurograde barge swaps were at $203/$204, down about $2 on late Tuesday talk.
Heating oil barges were down over $1 on IPE gas oil futures losses. Premiums were unchanged.
